adjectives.description: overweary (comparative more overweary, superlative most overweary)

entries.meaning: Overly weary; too tired or worn out.

verbs.description: overweary (third-person singular simple present overwearies, present participle overwearying, simple past and past participle overwearied)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To weary too much; to tire out.
examples: he hung down his head, as overwearied, and leaned upon his pulpit
